---
// Astro emits this as dist/404.html. Cloudflare Pages serves it (with a real
// 404 status) for any unmatched path — replacing the soft-404 fallback that
// silently served the homepage. Note: a zone-level catch-all redirect to "/"
// will shadow this until it is removed in Cloudflare.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Page not found" description="The page you requested could not be found.">
  <article class="reading">
    <h1>Page not found</h1>
    <p>
      The page you’re looking for doesn’t exist, or it may have moved. If you
      arrived here from a citation, check the URL — the published Commentary
      lives under <a href="/commentary/john/">Commentary</a>, and each unit has a
      stable canonical address (for example,
      <code>secnt.org/commentary/john/1-1-to-3/</code>).
    </p>
    <p>
      Return to the <a href="/">homepage</a>, or read the
      <a href="/commentary/john/">Commentary on the Gospel of John</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
